    "Therefore, we decouple these mechanisms to analyze how routing decisions impact server utilization and how batching strategies mitigate head-of-line blocking.",
    "Request Routing Strategies Figure 8 evaluates system performance by varying the number of draft models from 0.4k to 2.0k while comparing three routing strategies: Random, Round-Robin (RR), and Join-Shortest-Queue (JSQ), as described in Section 3.4.",
    "JSQ achieves the best performance when system resources are not fully utilized, maintaining TPOT values 5-20 ms lower across all traces by routing requests to less busy target servers.",
    "However, as the system approaches its maximum capacity, the fastest server remains saturated, causing subsequent requests already assigned to it to suffer from head-ofline blocking.",
    "As a result, the TPOT curve eventually rises above that of Round-Robin."
